<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4761b658-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7465"><num value="7465">§ 7465.</num><heading> Provisions of special application to transferees</heading><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I23" class="indent2 fontsize7" id="id4761b659-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7465/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> For rules of burden of proof in transferee proceedings, see section 6902(a).</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I23" class="indent2 fontsize7" id="id4761b65a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7465/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> For authority of Tax Court to prescribe rules by which a transferee of property of a taxpayer shall be entitled to examine books, records and other evidence, see section 6902(b).</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id4761b65b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/888">68A Stat. 888</ref>, § 7463; renumbered § 7464, <ref href="/us/pl/91/172/tIX/s957/a">Pub. L. 91–172, title IX, § 957(a)</ref>, <date date="1969-12-30">Dec. 30, 1969</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/83/733">83 Stat. 733</ref>; renumbered § 7465, <ref href="/us/pl/96/589/s6/c/1">Pub. L. 96–589, § 6(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="1980-12-24">Dec. 24, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/3407">94 Stat. 3407</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
